dives-under-harsh-braking-medium-elastomers-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-239696\">Testing the original carbon Fasst Flexx Enduro suspension handlebar – Photo by Innes Graham</figcaption></figure><p>Wait a second. A bendy bar? I must be mad, right? Well, maybe, but the fact that Fasst Co have been make suspension handlebars for motocross tells you these guys know what they’re doing. It is not a gimmick. They know how to make strong handlebars. This gave me the confidence to charge hard in testing. Read the complete long-term review <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/07/09/long-term-review-fasst-flexx-enduro-bar-takes-the-edge-off-hits-tuneable-to-your-ride/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version.jpg\" alt=\"fasst flexx alloy suspension handlebar 31.8mm clamp 25mm rise\" width=\"1200\" height=\"429\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-297x106.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-800x286.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-120x43.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-768x275.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-696x249.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-1068x382.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-1175x420.jpg 1175w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-297x106.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-800x286.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-120x43.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-768x275.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-696x249.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-1068x382.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-enduro-mtn-handlebar-aluminium-version-1175x420.jpg 1175w\"></a></p><p>As you can probably tell from all that hardware, these uniquely tuneable suspension handlebars for mountain biking are not lightweight. The carbon version we tested weighs in at 450g, while the new Flexx alloy bar weighs a claimed 550g. To put that into context, the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/02/03/nukeproof-horizon-v2-bar-chain-guide-and-ti-components-celebrate-brands-30th-year/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Nukeproof Horizon V2</a> 35mm clamp 25mm riser alloy bar weighs a claimed 290g. So, yeah, they are heavy. But it’s enduro and DH remember. We race down, not up!</p><figure id=\"attachment_251326\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251326\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar.jpg\"><img loading=\"eager\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng%3Awebp%2Fngcb8%2Frs%3Adevice%2Frscb8-1\" alt=\"fasst co flexx alloy enduro mtb handlebar\" width=\"1200\" height=\"790\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar-297x196.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar-800x527.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar-120x79.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar-768x506.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar-696x458.jpg 696w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar-1068x703.jpg 1068w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/fasst-flexx-alloy-mtb-bar-638x420.jpg 638w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251326\">Both the carbon and alloy Flexx bars have a 31.8mm diameter clamp area with a 25mm rise</figcaption></figure><p>We previously asked Chris Tidwell of Fasst Co why they opted for a carbon bar in the first instance. He said, <em>“When we started the project several years ago (2015), weight was more of a concern. Now several years later weight is less of a concern if durability, comfort or improved handling is gained as well.”</em></p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The new Flexx Alloy handlebar from Fasst Company is available now in 8° and 12° backsweep version for $324.99. That gets you an 800mm (Enduro) or an 810mm (DH) bar with four different sets of rebound and compression elastomers; soft, medium, hard and extra hard.&nbsp;<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-4\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://www.fasstco.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>FasstCo.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"86ebc3ff92c82576abfc05d7a8579e649e7a54c9ec785cb39d508fd6ce1fde5a","category":"Cycling"}